# Canvas Dashboard Overhaul ‚Äî Command Center Edition

Replace the current WrapPanel dashboard with a **Command Center** UI: a high-level **Home overview** as the landing page, a full **Canvas workspace** for deep sensor monitoring, and an "on-glass" navigation model that swaps views within a `TransitioningContentControl` (smooth crossfade transitions) ‚Äî no tabs.

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> **Home View pinned cards:** Users pin sensors to the Home overview via **right-click ‚Üí "üìå Pin to Home"** on any sensor card in the Canvas workspace (long-press on mobile). Pinned sensor IDs are persisted in the profile's `PinnedSensorIds` list.

> [!WARNING]
> **Breaking Change:** The existing `DashboardView.axaml` (WrapPanel layout) will be superseded by `HomeView.axaml` + `CanvasView.axaml`. The old file is preserved for reference but no longer wired.

---

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph LR
    A["MainWindow"] --> B["ShellView (ContentControl)"]
    B --> C["HomeView (Landing)"]
    B --> D["CanvasView (Workspace)"]
    B --> E["SettingsView"]
    C -- "Navigate ‚Üí" --> D
    C -- "‚öô Settings" --> E
    D -- "‚Üê Back" --> C
    E -- "‚Üê Back" --> C
```

**Navigation Model:** A `ShellViewModel` owns a `CurrentView` property. Buttons within each view swap the content ‚Äî no external tab strips, keeping everything "on-glass" inside the content area. This scales identically across Desktop and Android.

